---
import { grahamTests } from "../lib/graham.mjs";
import { TONE_COLOR } from "../lib/fundamentals.mjs";

const { company } = Astro.props;
const { tests, passes, testable } = grahamTests(company);

const TONE = { pass: "good", near: "warn", fail: "bad", na: "none" };
const LABEL = { pass: "Pass", near: "Near", fail: "Miss", na: "—" };
---

<section class="graham">
  <div class="head">
    <h2>Graham’s defensive-investor test</h2>
    {testable ? <span class="count">{passes} of {testable} met</span> : null}
  </div>

  <p class="intro">
    Graham gave the defensive investor seven numerical criteria in <em>The Intelligent Investor</em>.
    Here they are, run mechanically on the filings, his framework, not our verdict. Meeting them is a
    floor of safety, not a reason to buy; missing one is no veto, since many fine modern businesses fail
    his strictest liquidity tests by design. The worth is in seeing exactly where a company stands against
    the canon, every number sourced.
  </p>

  <ul class="tests">
    {tests.map((t) => (
      <li>
        <div class="row">
          <span class="name">{t.name}</span>
          <span class="badge" style={`color:${TONE_COLOR[TONE[t.status]]}; border-color:${TONE_COLOR[TONE[t.status]]}`}>{LABEL[t.status]}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="crit">{t.criterion} · <b>{t.value}</b></div>
        <p class="note">{t.note}</p>
      </li>
    ))}
  </ul>

  <p class="foot">Graham would be the first to say a checklist is a starting point, not an answer. These are his <em>defensive, bargain-hunter's</em> tests, the cigar-butt lens. Buffett and Munger grew past it, paying fair prices for wonderful businesses; that lens lives in the moat and owner-earnings work above, and both still matter. Clearing Graham’s tests earns a closer look; failing them earns harder questions, not a dismissal.</p>
</section>

<style>
  .graham { border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); padding: 20px 22px; margin: 20px 0; background: #fff; }
  .head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .head h2 { margin: 0; }
  .count { font-size: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--muted); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; flex: 0 0 auto; }

  .intro { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--muted); margin: 10px 0 0; line-height: 1.55; max-width: 70ch; }

  .tests { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 16px 0 0; }
  .tests li { padding: 12px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .row { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
  .name { font-weight: 600; font-size: 16px; }
  .badge { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 10.5px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.07em; text-transform: uppercase; border: 1px solid; border-radius: 2px; padding: 1px 7px; flex: 0 0 auto; }
  .crit { font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); margin-top: 3px; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .crit b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .note { font-size: 13px; color: #3a3e46; margin: 5px 0 0; line-height: 1.5; }

  .foot { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); margin-top: 14px; padding-top: 11px; }
</style>
